          "body": "9:11-14 is the chapter's argumentative pivot. Christ appeared as high priest of the good things to come, entered through the greater and more perfect tabernacle (heaven itself, not made with hands), and entered *not through the blood of goats and calves but through His own blood, once for all, having obtained eternal redemption*. The trinitarian density of 9:14 is staggering: Christ *offered Himself* (the Son) *through the eternal Spirit* (the Spirit) *without blemish to God* (the Father). This is not just substitution; it is a triune transaction in which the cleansing reaches the conscience (*suneidēsin*) — the very faculty the old cultus could not touch — and the result is positive vocation: *to serve the living God*. The pastoral payoff is precise: a cleansed conscience for the purpose of serving worship."
